content.text:
Good. The sidebar.tsx uses Tailwind classes like `bg-sidebar`, `text-sidebar-foreground`, `border-sidebar-border`, `bg-sidebar-accent`, `text-sidebar-accent-foreground`, `ring-sidebar-ring`, `bg-sidebar-primary`, `text-sidebar-primary-foreground`. These all reference `--color-sidebar-*` Tailwind theme tokens which currently have NO definition in `index.css`. This is a critical gap.

Now I have enough information to design a comprehensive implementation plan.

---

## Detailed Implementation Plan: Custom Theme System for T3 Code

### 1. Architecture Overview

The design follows three layers:

**Layer 1 -- Shared type definitions + built-in theme data** (`packages/shared/src/theme.ts`)
Contains the `Theme` type, the `ThemeColors` interface, and the three built-in theme objects with their concrete color values. This lives in `packages/shared` (not `contracts`) because theme objects contain runtime data (color values), and `contracts` must remain schema-only per AGENTS.md.

**Layer 2 -- Theme engine** (`apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts`)
Replaces the existing light/dark/system hook. Manages theme selection, localStorage persistence, CSS variable application, FOUC prevention, cross-tab sync, and OS preference detection. The hook continues to use `useSyncExternalStore` with module-level initialization.

**Layer 3 -- UI integration** (settings page, CSS, components)
Theme selector with swatches on the settings page; CSS variable definitions for new tokens (sidebar, editor, terminal, statusBar); updated consumers.

### 2. File-by-File Implementation

---

#### 2.1 NEW: `packages/shared/src/theme.ts`

**Purpose**: Central type definitions and built-in theme data.

**Type definitions**:

```typescript
/** Base appearance: determines .dark class on documentElement */
export type ThemeAppearance = "light" | "dark";

/** Identifies a built-in theme */
export type ThemeId = "t3-light" | "t3-dark" | "t3-midnight";

/** Special value allowing auto-selection based on OS preference */
export type ThemePreference = ThemeId | "system";

/** Color region: groups of semantically related color tokens */
export interface ThemeColorRegion {
  readonly background: string;
  readonly foreground: string;
  readonly accent: string;
  readonly accentForeground: string;
  readonly border: string;
}

/** Full color specification for a theme */
export interface ThemeColors {
  // Core tokens (override the :root / @variant dark defaults)
  readonly background: string;
  readonly foreground: string;
  readonly primary: string;
  readonly primaryForeground: string;
  readonly accent: string;
  readonly accentForeground: string;
  readonly muted: string;
  readonly mutedForeground: string;
  readonly card: string;
  readonly cardForeground: string;
  readonly popover: string;
  readonly popoverForeground: string;
  readonly border: string;
  readonly input: string;
  readonly ring: string;
  // Region-specific tokens
  readonly sidebar: ThemeColorRegion;
  readonly editor: ThemeColorRegion;
  readonly terminal: ThemeColorRegion;
  readonly statusBar: ThemeColorRegion;
}

/** A complete theme definition */
export interface Theme {
  readonly id: ThemeId;
  readonly name: string;
  readonly appearance: ThemeAppearance;
  readonly colors: ThemeColors;
}
```

**Built-in themes** (three constant objects):

- **`T3_LIGHT`** -- `appearance: "light"`. White/neutral-based. Background `#ffffff`, foreground `#1e293b` (slate-800 equivalent). Sidebar slightly tinted `#f8fafc` (slate-50). Editor white. Terminal `#1e293b` bg with `#e2e8f0` fg (dark terminal). StatusBar `#f1f5f9`.

- **`T3_DARK`** -- `appearance: "dark"`. The current dark palette, aligned with existing `@variant dark` values. Background `#0a0a0b` (near-black), foreground `#f1f5f9`. Sidebar `#111113`. Editor `#0a0a0b`. Terminal `#0a0a0b` bg with `#e2e8f0` fg. StatusBar `#111113`.

- **`T3_MIDNIGHT`** -- `appearance: "dark"`. Deep navy/indigo-tinted. Background `#0f172a` (slate-900), foreground `#e2e8f0`. Primary shifted to indigo `oklch(0.65 0.2 270)`. Sidebar `#1e1b4b` (indigo-950). Editor `#0f172a`. Terminal `#020617` (slate-950) with `#cbd5e1` fg. StatusBar `#1e1b4b`.

**Exports**:

```typescript
export const BUILT_IN_THEMES: readonly Theme[] = [T3_LIGHT, T3_DARK, T3_MIDNIGHT];

export function getThemeById(id: ThemeId): Theme;
export function getDefaultThemeForAppearance(appearance: ThemeAppearance): Theme;

/** Returns the two system-cycle themes for OS preference matching */
export const SYSTEM_THEME_LIGHT: ThemeId = "t3-light";
export const SYSTEM_THEME_DARK: ThemeId = "t3-dark";
```

---

#### 2.2 MODIFY: `packages/shared/package.json`

Add a new subpath export (following the existing pattern -- no barrel, explicit subpath):

```json
