### 3. CSS Variable Application Strategy

The theme engine in `useTheme.ts` applies all CSS custom properties to `document.documentElement.style`. The mapping from `ThemeColors` to CSS variables is:

| ThemeColors path | CSS variable set on `<html>` |
|---|---|
| `colors.background` | `--background` |
| `colors.foreground` | `--foreground` |
| `colors.primary` | `--primary` |
| `colors.primaryForeground` | `--primary-foreground` |
| `colors.accent` | `--accent` |
| `colors.accentForeground` | `--accent-foreground` |
| `colors.muted` | `--muted` |
| `colors.mutedForeground` | `--muted-foreground` |
| `colors.card` | `--card` |
| `colors.cardForeground` | `--card-foreground` |
| `colors.popover` | `--popover` |
| `colors.popoverForeground` | `--popover-foreground` |
| `colors.border` | `--border` |
| `colors.input` | `--input` |
| `colors.ring` | `--ring` |
| `colors.sidebar.background` | `--sidebar-background` |
| `colors.sidebar.foreground` | `--sidebar-foreground` |
| `colors.sidebar.accent` | `--sidebar-accent` |
| `colors.sidebar.accentForeground` | `--sidebar-accentForeground` |
| `colors.sidebar.border` | `--sidebar-border` |
| `colors.editor.*` | `--editor-*` |
| `colors.terminal.*` | `--terminal-*` |
| `colors.statusBar.*` | `--statusBar-*` |

The implementation in `applyTheme` uses a helper function:

```typescript
function setCSSVariables(theme: Theme): void {
  const root = document.documentElement;
  const { colors } = theme;

  // Flat core tokens
  const coreTokens: Array<[string, string]> = [
    ["--background", colors.background],
    ["--foreground", colors.foreground],
    ["--primary", colors.primary],
    ["--primary-foreground", colors.primaryForeground],
    // ... all flat tokens
  ];

  // Region tokens
  const regions = ["sidebar", "editor", "terminal", "statusBar"] as const;
  for (const region of regions) {
    const regionColors = colors[region];
    for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(regionColors)) {
      coreTokens.push([`--${region}-${key}`, value]);
    }
  }

  for (const [prop, value] of coreTokens) {
    root.style.setProperty(prop, value);
  }
}
```

When the theme changes, all properties are overwritten. The `:root` CSS rules serve as fallbacks only for the initial render before JS loads.

